article.description: — Justin Hill had 23 points as Longwood edged past Presbyterian 71-70 on Saturday.
article.headline: Hill scores 23 to lead Longwood past Presbyterian 71-70
article.linkText: Hill scores 23 to lead Longwood past Presbyterian 71-70
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- — Justin Hill had 23 points as Longwood edged past Presbyterian 71-70 on Saturday. Hill made 10 of 11 free throws. DeShaun Wade had 17 points for Longwood (12-5, 4-0 Big South Conference), which earned its fifth consecutive victory. Rayshon Harrison had 29 points for the Blue Hose (8-12, 0-5), who have now lost five consecutive games. Trevon Reddish-Rhone added 12 points. Winston Hill had seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
